#direction: right
[Freezable|Defines an object that has a modifiable stat and a read-only (frozen) state. Classes that derive from Freezable provide detailed change notification, can be made immutable, and can clone themselves.]
[Animatable|Abstract class that provides animation support.]
[VisualBrush|Paints an area with a Visual.]
[TileBrush|Describes a way to paint a region by using one or more tiles.]
[TileBrush|Describes a way to paint a region by using one or more tiles.]
[Brush|Defines objects used to paint graphical objects. Classes that derive from Brush describe how the area is painted.]
[GradientBrush|An abstract class that describes a gradient, composed of gradient stops. Classes that inherit from GradientBrush describe different ways of interpreting gradient stops.]
[SolidColorBrush|Paints an area with a solid color.]
[ImageBrush|Paints an area with an image.]
[DrawingBrush|Paints an area with a Drawing, which can include shapes, text, video, images, or other drawings.]
[BitmapCacheBrush|Paints an area with cached content.]
[LinearGradientBrush|Paints an area with a linear gradient.]
[RadialGradientBrush|Paints an area with a radial gradient. A focal point defines the beginning of the gradient, and a circle defines the end point of the gradient.]
[ImageSource|Represents an object type that has a width, height, and ImageMetadata such as a BitmapSource and a DrawingImage. This is an abstract class.]
[BitmapSource|Represents a single, constant set of pixels at a certain size and resolution.]
[BitmapImage|Provides a specialized BitmapSource that is optimized for loading images using Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML).]
[InteropBitmap|InteropBitmap enables developers to improve rendering performance of non-WPF UIs that are hosted by WPF in interoperability scenarios.]
[BitmapFrame|Represents image data returned by a decoder and accepted by encoders.]
[CachedBitmap|Provides caching functionality for a BitmapSource.]
[ColorConvertedBitmap|Changes the color space of a BitmapSource.]
[FormatConvertedBitmap|Provides pixel format conversion functionality for a BitmapSource.]
[RenderTargetBitmap|Converts a Visual object into a bitmap.]
[TransformedBitmap|Scales and rotates a BitmapSource.]
[WriteableBitmap|Provides a BitmapSource that can be written to and updated.]
[CroppedBitmap|Crops a BitmapSource.]
[DrawingImage|An ImageSource that uses a Drawing for content.]
[D3DImage|An ImageSource that displays a user-created Direct3D surface.]
[Brush] <:- [SolidColorBrush] [DependencyObject] <:- [Freezable] <:- [Animatable] <:- [Brush]
[ImageSource] <:- [D3DImage] [ImageSource] <:- [DrawingImage]
[Brush] <:- [GradientBrush] <:- [LinearGradientBrush] [GradientBrush] <:- [RadialGradientBrush]
[Drawing|Abstract class that describes a 2-D drawing. This class cannot be inherited by your code.]
[DrawingGroup|Represents a collection of drawings that can be operated upon as a single drawing.]
[GeometryDrawing|Draws a Geometry using the specified Brush and Pen.]
[GlyphRunDrawing|Represents a Drawing object that renders a GlyphRun.]
[ImageDrawing|Draws an image within a region defined by a Rect.]
[VideoDrawing|Plays a media file. If the media is a video file, the VideoDrawing draws it to the specified rectangle.]
[Pen|Describes how a shape is outlined.]
